			<staticText>
				<reportElement stretchType="RelativeToBandHeight" x="30" y="30" width="239" height="60" uuid="b0bd2e0b-7eb3-4ce3-b186-cc9b1054cfba"/>
				<textElement>
					<font fontName="DejaVu Sans Mono" size="12" isBold="false"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[ declaration added to invoices by businesses not required to generate e-invoices, often confirming their turnover is below the mandatory threshold.
Preferential Origin: In international trade, exporters use this to declare that goods meet specific rules, allowing for reduced or zero import duties.
Accuracy & Compliance: A statement certifying that the invoice shows the actual price, quantity, and description of goods.
Contents: Typically includes the seller's declaration, signature, date, and sometimes PAN or GSTIN details. 
Business.gov.nl
Business.gov.nl
 +5
Sample Declaration for E-Invoice Exemption (India):
"We, [Company Name], hereby declare that our aggregate turnover for any of the F.Y. [20XX-XX] to [20XX-XX] does not exceed the prescribed threshold for generating a Unique Invoice Registration Number (IRN) and QR code as per the provisions of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017". 
BELSITE | WEBPORTAL
BELSITE | WEBPORTAL
Sample Declaration for Export/Goods Value:
"We declare that this invoice shows the actual price of the goods described and that all particulars are true and correct". 
